FBIS3-54741 "drsov001_b_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Khasbulatov Applies for Release, Cites Absence of Evidence LD3012150793 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1430 GMT 30 Dec 93 LD3012150793 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Ruslan Khasbulatov, the former speaker of the Russian parliament, who was arrested in connection with the events of 3 and 4 October in Moscow, and his lawyer Vladimir Fomichev, have put in an application to have the criminal charges quashed and to be released from custody owing to the absence of a corpus delicti in the actions of Khasbulatov. It was reported to INTERFAX today by lawyer Fomichev that since the arrest on 4 October Khasbulatov has still not had evidence submitted to him confirming his guilt.
